- > the time for pod  to come back online pod evicition timeout
kubectl-controller-manager pod-eviction timeout 5 minutes
Drain : evicted pod and create new pod from other node.
Cordon: Simply marks a node unscheduleable, Unlike drain it does not terminate or move the pods other node

kubectl drain node1 --ignore-deamonset
If a pod has no connection between repl≈üca set, you have to force to drain and pod can be lost forever.
